description:
Create TypeScript interfaces for race weekend widget data in the frontend.

## Types to Create (in web/src/types/api.ts)

```typescript
interface RaceSession {
  session_type: 'fp1' | 'fp2' | 'fp3' | 'qualifying' | 'sprint_qualifying' | 'sprint_race' | 'race';
  start_time: string; // ISO 8601 UTC
  end_time: string;
  status: 'scheduled' | 'completed';
}

interface RaceWeekendSchedule {
  season: number;
  round: number;
  race_name: string;
  circuit_name: string;
  circuit_country: string;
  sessions: RaceSession[];
  is_sprint_weekend: boolean;
}

interface SessionResult {
  position: number;
  driver_code: string;
  driver_name: string;
  team: string;
  time?: string;
  gap?: string;
  laps?: number;
  points?: number;
}

interface SessionResults {
  session_type: string;
  results: SessionResult[];
}

interface CircuitHistory {
  previous_year: {
    winner: { driver: string; team: string };
    second: { driver: string; team: string };
    third: { driver: string; team: string };
    pole: { driver: string; team: string };
    fastest_lap: { driver: string; time: string };
  } | null;
}
```

## API Functions to Create (in web/src/lib/api.ts)
- fetchRaceWeekendSchedule(season, round)
- fetchSessionResults(season, round, sessionType)
- fetchCircuitHistory(season, circuitId)

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All types match backend API responses
- [ ] API functions handle errors gracefully
- [ ] Types are exported and available to components
